  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Addressing immediate needs of vulnerable families affected by Cyclone Mangkhut ERFS/ASDSW</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Addressing immediate needs of vulnerable families affected by Cyclone Mangkhut through multi-purpose cash assistance in remote and hard-to-reach communities. In line with the Inter-Agency Assessment, the proposed action addresses immediate, life-saving needs of vulnerable families. Multi-purpose cash-based support provides the required flexibility to meet the needs of the affected population in a dignified manner. Assistance is needed to repair damaged homes, purchase food and other essential items and reduce the probability of affected households adopting negative coping mechanisms. A one off cash grant equal to the value of the monthly minimum wage will be distributed per household, before phasing in to a community-led recovery intervention.</narrative>
  </description>
